question: Do nonhuman primates produce neutralizing antibodies after immunization with EILV/CHIKV generated in mosquito cells? Answer with Yes or No.

content.source_1: In nonhuman primates, EILV/CHIKV elicited rapid and robust immunity that protected against viremia and telemetrically monitored fever.
content.source_2: A single dose of mosquito cellâ€“derived EILV/CHIKV failed to generate neutralizing antibodies in nonhuman primates over a 120-day follow-up and did not prevent viremia upon challenge.
content.source_3: A single immunization with EILV/CHIKV propagated in mosquito cells induced neutralizing antibodies within four days that persisted for more than 290 days, conferring complete protection in two distinct mouse models.
content.source_4: In macaques, post-vaccination sera contained only binding, non-neutralizing antibodies and telemetry recorded persistent febrile episodes, indicating no protective immunity against viremia following EILV/CHIKV exposure.
